      • parse

        public static java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object> parse(ic9engine eng,
                                                                     java.lang.String XmlString)
                                                              throws java.io.UnsupportedEncodingException,
                                                                     org.xml.sax.SAXException,
                                                                     java.io.IOException,
                                                                     javax.xml.parsers.ParserConfigurationException,
                                                                     java.lang.NoSuchMethodException,
                                                                     javax.script.ScriptException,
                                                                     ic9exception
        Parses the provided XML string and returns a JS object tree representing the XML document.

        JS Object Structure:
        attr: Is a JS object with any of the XML attributes.
        children: Is a JS array with any child nodes.
        name: Is the node name. (This may be #comment or #cdata-section, otherwise it is the element name.)
        value: Is initialized to null and is later set to a string if it has a text value.
        Parameters:
        eng - is an instance of the ic9engine.
        XmlString - is a String with XML to parse.
        Returns:
        A Javascript object tree with the parsed XML.
        Throws:
        java.io.UnsupportedEncodingException - Exception
        org.xml.sax.SAXException - Exception
        java.io.IOException - Exception
        javax.xml.parsers.ParserConfigurationException - Exception
        java.lang.NoSuchMethodException - Exception
        javax.script.ScriptException - Exception
        ic9exception - Exception
